    <briefdescription>
<para>Pluggable logging sink. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classiceberg_1_1Logger_1ae94e42dfc0fe122f056c54049f6b751f" kindref="member">ShouldLog()</ref> is the single authority for runtime filtering <ndash/> the macros call it on every (compile-time-enabled) statement, so level changes by any path take effect immediately. Implementations must be thread-safe and must not throw. They must also obey:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>No reentrancy: <ref refid="classiceberg_1_1Logger_1a2cea7121351c84e8fe25a4fb2a1e52a3" kindref="member">Log()</ref>/Flush() must not call the logging macros or GetDefaultLogger() (UB <ndash/> deadlock with mutex-based sinks).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="classiceberg_1_1Logger_1a8d7d6a59ecbb0a1ba0ca79cbbb079540" kindref="member">level()</ref> is an accessor consistent with ShouldLog (used by SetDefaultLevel and introspection); ShouldLog may implement finer logic than a level compare. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
